column3: detail
Topham Guerin was awarded a £3 million contract by the Cabinet Office to work on COVID-19 messaging without tender
Ben Guerin is a founding partner of Topham Guerin
Sean Topham is a founding partner of Topham Guerin

Topham Guerin was hired to run digital campaign strategy for the Conservatives in the 2019 election, including a stunt where the Conservative party Twitter account was renamed "factcheckUK" in an attempt to mislead users
Michael Gove is a Conservative MP and Minister for the Cabinet Office
Public First was awarded an £840,000 contract by the Cabinet Office without open tender
James Frayne is a founding partner of PR firm Public First
James Frayne was a founding member of New Frontiers Foundation, a rightwing think tank
Dominic Cummings was a founding member of New Frontiers Foundation, a rightwing think tank
Rachel Wolf is a founding partner of PR firm Public First
Rachel Wolf is a former adviser to Michael Gove
Rachel Wolf co-wrote the 2019 Tory manifesto
James Frayne was a policy research for "Business for Sterling", a campaign against Britain joining the Euro
Dominic Cummings was campaign director at "Business for Sterling", a campaign against Britain joining the Euro
Dominic Cummings is Chief Adivsor to the Prime Minister, and previously served as Director of Strategy for then-leader Iain Duncan-Smith in 2002
Dominic Cummings was a Special Adviser to Michael Gove at Department for Education, 2011-2014
Rachel Wolf founded the New Schools Network
Dominic Cummings worked as a paid freelancer for the New Schools Network in 2010
Dominic Cummings served as a Communications adviser for Babylon Health until 2018
Matt Hancock appeared in a paid "advertorial" for Babylon Health in the Evening Standard
Matt Hancock is a Conservative MP and government minister
Globus (Shetland) has donated more than £350,000 to the Tories since 2016
Globus (Shetland) one of several firms awarded a £93 million PPE contract by the UK government
The Conservatives have been in government since 2010 (in coalition) and since 2015 as a single-party government
Boris Johnson is the Prime Minister
Boris Johnson is a Conservative MP and currently Prime Minister
The Prime Minister regularly attends private dinners and drinks receptions with this group of wealthy Tory donors
Agustsson is CEO of Globus Group

Serco has been awarded several large government contracts, including a contact-tracing contract that is reportedly worth up to £410 million and a contract for COVID-19 testing centres worth £57 million
Edward Argar is a Conservative MP and government minister
Edward Argar is a Conservative MP and government minister
Edward Argar was formerly head of UK and Europe public affairs at Serco
Rupert and Nicholas Soames are brothers
Nicholas Soames was a Conservative MP
Randox has been awarded contracts for COVID-19 testing worth nearly £500 million unopposed, despite the company having to recall tests over the summer due to fears of contamination
Conservative MP Owen Paterson is paid £100,000 per year by Randox to serve as a "consultant"
Think tank "UK 2020" founded by Conservative MP Owen Patterson
Conservative MP Owen Paterson received at least £39,000 from unknown donors to fund overseas trips via his thinktank "UK 2020"
Randox sponsored a "UK 2020" report
Christopher Bullivant was a member of rightwing think tank "UK 2020"
Conservative MP Owen Paterson granted Christopher Bullivant a parliamentary pass
Owen Paterson was married to Matt Ridley's sister Rose Paterson
P14 Medical was awarded a £156 million contract to import PPE from China, without any competition
Steve Dechan, a Conservative local councillor, is the founder of P14 Medical
Ayanda Capital, a family investment fund with no prior links to the healthcare sector, was awarded a £252 million contract to supply face masks, which were then found to be faulty
Andrew Mills is an adviser to Tory minister Liz Truss
Andrew Mills was an adviser to Ayanda Capital and brokered the deal under which Ayanda was to provide 50 million face masks to the UK government
Dido Harding is married to Conservative MP John Penrose
John Penrose formerly worked at McKinsey
Dido Harding formerly worked at McKinsey
David Cameron and Dido Harding are friends and attended Oxford University together
Anthony Page founded PPE Medpro in 2020, just a month before it was awarded a large government contract
PPE Medro was awarded a £122 million contract to supply PPE to the NHS
Before founding PPE Medpro, Anthony Page was the secretary of the company which manages Michelle Mone's "brand"
Dido Harding runs the NHS Test and Trace program
Douglas Barrowman founded the Knox group of companies
Douglas Barrowman and Michelle Mone are engaged
Lancaster Knox has given over £200,000 to the Conservative party since 2017
Rupert Soames is CEO of outsourcing company Serco
Matt Ridley is a Conservative hereditary peer
Owen Paterson is a Conservative MP
John Penrose is a Conservative MP
David Cameron was a Conservative Prime Minister
Liz Truss is a Conservative MP and minister
Steve Dechan is a Conservative local councillor for Stroud
Michelle Mone was made into a Conservative peer by David Cameron in 2015
Anthony Page is the Director of the Family Office at Knox House Trust
Knox House Trust is part of the Knox group of companies
Lancaster Knox is part of the Knox group of companies

Billionaire Douglas Barrowman tried to donate £2,500 to the Tories in 2019, but it was returned since he was not on the electoral register at the time, making him an "impermissible donor" under the current rules.
Andrew and Deborah Feldman are siblings
Andrew Feldman was made a Conservative peer in 2010 and previously served as co-chairman of the Conservative party

Andrew Feldman has been described as David Cameron's oldest political friend". Feldman ran fundraising for Cameron's successful Tory leadership bid in 2005. Camerson subsequently made Feldman a life peer in 2010.
Deborah Feldman is a Managing Director at Topham Guerin
Andrew Feldman created London-based clothing company Jayroma, and used it to funnel tens of thousands of pounds in donations to the Conservative party
Andrew Feldman used his clothing company to funnel over £100,000 in donations to the Conservative party
Jayroma, the clothing company run by Andrew Feldman, donated £10,000 to David Cameron's leadership campaign in 2005
Kate Bingham is married to Conservative MP and government minister Jesse Norman
Kate Bingham was appointed to run the UK Vaccine Taskforce
Patrick Vallance is the Chief Scientific Adviser to the UK government
Patrick Vallance was president of research and development at GlaxoSmithKline (GSK) from 2012 to 2018. Vallance currently holds £600,000 worth of GSK shares as part of a deferred bonus.
Rachel and Boris Johnson are siblings
Kate Bingham and Rachel Johnson went to school together at St Paul's Girls' School
Rachel and Jo Johnson are siblings
Boris and Jo Johnson are siblings. Boris Johnson elevated his brother Jo to the House of Lords in the 2019 honours list.
Rachel Johnson is married to Ivo Dawnay
Tom Bingham and Ivo Dawnay are cousins
Kate Bingham is the daughter of Tom Bingham
Ivo Dawnay ran Tom Bingham's campaign to be chancellor of Oxford University in 2003
Max Johnson is a half-brother to Boris Johnson
Max Johnson joined the board of REVIV Global, whose medical director said he hoped the appointment would "open doors" for the company.
REVIV Global is reportedly in talks with the UK government about providing COVID-19 testing
Haraldur Agustsson is part of the exclusive "Leaders' Club" for wealthy Conservative donors
Globus (Shetland) is part of Globus Group
Alpha Solway is part of Globus Group
Alpha Solway has been awarded several large contracts by the Scottish government, including a £53 million contract to provide PPEE to NHS Scotland
Ayanda Capital is registered in Mauritius, a notorious tax haven
Knox House Trust is registered in the Isle of Man, a tax haven

Jesse Norman is a Conservative MP and government minister
